Wow September here we are. Let’s let’s bring on the Fall DIY’S and Decor✨
⠀⠀⠀⠀
Here is a Quivk DIY I did last fall. I wanted to add a dusting of glitter to my pumpkins, leaves, and acorns. Glam them up but still see the natural coloring, without fully covering. I love the look✨
⠀
Canisters are ON SALE and they are linked in my stories now. Head over there to swipe up and shop✨
⠀
Pumpkin mix is from Ross. Use Mod PODGE glue to adhere the glitter✨
⠀

node.text:
DIY Glam Pumpkins✨
⠀
Ok so who’s ready for the fall?!! Welp
I’m not. But hey here are some Glam DIY Pumpkins I did last fall. And they got a quick lil feature on the Tamron Hall show!!✨
⠀
Quick and easy to make with velvet fabric from Hobby Lobby and Joann Fabric & Craft. I use mod podge glue to adhere the glitter and hot glue gun for the beads. Have fun with it and add glitter, beads etc. The possibilities are endless and there is no wrong. Just have fun with it✨
⠀

My LAUNDRY ROOM REVEAL✨
⠀⠀
Ok guys so here is the reveal!!! I still have a few more things to add. But for the most part it’s done!! Once again I wanna give a huge shout out to @modularclosets 👏🏽✨
⠀⠀⠀
Thank you to @modularclosets. I love my new laundry room system. Their team provides FREE DESIGN quotes, and made this process so easy. @christinagiaquinto their organizing expert, helped me figure out how I can best organize my laundry room✨
⠀⠀⠀⠀
Head to my stories and use my link for 15% off at @modularclosets✨
⠀⠀
I used a bunch of items I picked up from Homegoods to style it. And of course do you spot all the beauties from @cfadesigngroup. Yes the gold planters and florals are all from @cfadesigngroup✨
⠀⠀
Also Thank you once again to @wallcoveringsmart for the gorgeous wallpaper and @styleuphome for the gorgeous lighting✨
⠀⠀
You can shop my area rugs and gold step stool by clicking link in my BIO✨
⠀⠀
